      "(hasDerivAt_id x) 1` to get `hasDerivAt (fun x ↦ x/1) 1 x`, but perhaps we want something else?\n\nActually, perhaps easier:\n`HasDerivAt.div (hasDerivAt_const x 1) (hasDerivAt_id x) (by ...)` gives derivative of `1/x` at `x`, which is `-1/x²`.\n\nAlternatively, we know that the derivative of `1/x` is `-1/x²`, so perhaps we can use `HasDerivAt.const_div (hasDerivAt_id x) 1`? No, because that would give `(1 : ℝ) * (1 / x²)` but actually we need the derivative of `1 / x`.\n\nAlternatively, perhaps we can use the following:\n`(fun x ↦ 1/x)` is `(fun x ↦ x⁻¹)`, whose derivative is `-x⁻²`.\n\nThus, `hasDerivAt (fun x ↦ x⁻¹) (-x⁻²) x`, provided `x ≠ 0`.\n\nTherefore, we have `hasDerivAt (fun x ↦ Real.log x) (1/x) x` and `hasDerivAt (fun x ↦ x⁻¹) (-x⁻²) x`, and hence for `F(x) = Real.log x - x⁻¹`, we have `hasDerivAt F (1/x - (-x⁻²)) x = (1/x + x⁻²) x`.\n\nBut `x⁻²` is `1/x²`, and Lean",
      "\n    intro h\n    simp [uIcc, Real.uIcc_of_le, ha.le, hb.le] at h\n    <;>\n    (try { cases' h with h h <;> linarith }) <;>\n    (try { cases' h with h₁ h₂ <;> linarith }) <;>\n    (try { cases' h with h₁ h₂ <;> linarith })\n\n  have h₁ : ∫ x in a..b, (1 / x + 1 / x ^ 2 : ℝ) = (log b + 1 / a - log a - 1 / b : ℝ) := by\n    -- Use the fundamental theorem of calculus to evaluate the integral\n    have h₂ : ∫ x in a..b, (1 / x + 1 / x ^ 2 : ℝ) = (log b - log a) + (1 / a - 1 / b : ℝ) := by\n      -- Split the integral into two parts and evaluate each part separately\n      have h₃ : ∫ x in a..b, (1 / x + 1 / x ^ 2 : ℝ) = (∫ x in a..b, (1 / x : ℝ)) + ∫ x in a..b, (1 / x ^ 2 : ℝ) := by\n        -- Use the linearity of the integral\n        apply intervalIntegral.integral_add\n        · -- Prove that 1/x is integrable on [a, b]\n          apply Continuous.intervalIntegrable\n          exact continuousOn_const.div continuousOn_id (fun x hx => by\n            -- Since x ∈ [a, b] and a, b > 0, x > 0\n            have h₄ : a ≤ x := by exact hx.1\n            have h₅ : x ≤ b := by exact hx.2\n            have h₆ : 0 < a := ha\n            have h₇ : 0 < x := by linarith\n            exact by positivity)\n        · -- Prove that 1/x² is integrable on [a, b]\n          apply Continuous.intervalIntegrable\n          exact ContinuousOn.div (continuousOn_const) (continuousOn_pow 2) (fun x hx => by\n            -- Since x ∈ [a, b] and a, b > 0, x > 0\n            have h₄ : a ≤ x := by exact hx.1\n            have h₅ : x ≤ b := by exact hx.2\n            have h₆ : 0 < a := ha\n            have h₇ : 0 < x := by linarith\n            positivity)\n      -- Evaluate the integral of 1/x\n      have h₄ : ∫ x in a..b, (1 / x : ℝ) = log b - log a := by\n        -- Use the fundamental theorem of calculus\n        have h₅ : ∫ x in a..b, (1 / x : ℝ) = log b - log a := by\n          rw [← Real.log_div (by positivity) (by positivity)]\n          <;> simp [ha.ne', hb.ne']\n          <;>\n          simp_all [intervalIntegral.integral_comp_mul_left (fun x => 1 / x)]\n          <;>\n          field_simp [ha.ne', hb.ne']\n          <;>\n          ring_nf\n          <;>\n          norm_num\n          <;>\n          linarith\n        exact h₅\n      -- Evaluate the integral of 1/x²\n      have h₅ : ∫ x in a..b, (1 / x ^ 2 : ℝ) = (1 / a - 1 / b : ℝ) := by\n        -- Use the fundamental theorem of calculus\n        have h₆ : ∫ x in a..b, (1 / x ^ 2 : ℝ) = ∫ x in a..b, (x ^ (-2 : ℝ) : ℝ) := by\n          congr\n          funext x\n          rw [show (1 : ℝ) / x ^ 2 = x ^ (-2 : ℝ) by\n            {\n              field_simp [Real.rpow_neg, Real.rpow_two]\n              <;> ring_nf\n              <;> field_simp [Real.rpow_neg, Real.rpow_two]\n              <;> ring_nf\n            }]\n        rw [h₆]\n        -- Use the power rule for integration\n        have h₇ : ∫ x in a..b, (x ^ (-2 : ℝ) : ℝ) = (1 / a - 1 / b : ℝ) := by\n          have h₈ : ∫ x in a..b, (x ^ (-2 : ℝ) : ℝ) = (∫ x in a..b, (x ^ (-2 : ℝ) : ℝ)) := rfl\n          rw [h₈]\n          -- Use the power rule for integration\n          have h₉ : ∫ x in a..b, (x ^ (-2 : ℝ) : ℝ) = (1 / a - 1 / b : ℝ) := by\n            -- Use the fundamental theorem of calculus\n            have h₁₀ : ∫ x in a..b, (x ^ (-2 : ℝ) : ℝ) = ( ( (-2 : ℝ) + 1 : ℝ)⁻¹ * b ^ ((-2 : ℝ) + 1 : ℝ) - ( (-2 : ℝ) + 1 : ℝ)⁻¹ * a ^ ((-2 : ℝ) + 1 : ℝ) ) := by\n              -- Use the power rule for integration\n              rw [intervalIntegral.integral_rpow] <;>\n              (try norm_num) <;>\n              (try linarith) <;>\n              (try positivity) <;>\n              (try\n                {\n                  norm_num at *\n                  <;>\n                  linarith\n                })\n              <;>\n              (try\n                {\n                  linarith\n                })\n            rw [h₁₀]\n            -- Simplify the expression\n            have h₁₁ : ((-2 : ℝ) + 1 : ℝ)⁻¹ * b ^ ((-2 : ℝ) + 1 : ℝ) - ((-2 : ℝ) + 1 : ℝ)⁻¹ * a ^ ((-2 : ℝ) + 1 : ℝ) = (1 / a - 1 / b : ℝ) := by\n              have h₁₂ : ((-2 : ℝ) + 1 : ℝ) = (-1 : ℝ) := by norm_num\n              rw [h₁₂]\n              have h₁₃ : ((-1 : ℝ) : ℝ)⁻¹ = (-1 : ℝ) := by norm_num\n              rw [h₁₃]\n              have h₁₄ : (b : ℝ) ^ ((-1 : ℝ) : ℝ) = 1 / b := by\n                rw [Real.rpow_neg_one]\n                <;> field_simp\n              have h₁₅ : (a : ℝ) ^ ((-1 : ℝ) : ℝ) = 1 / a := by\n                rw [Real.rpow_neg_one]\n                <;> field_simp\n              rw [h₁₄, h₁₅]\n              <;> ring_nf\n              <;> field_simp\n              <;> ring_nf\n            rw [h₁₁]\n          rw [h₉]\n        rw [h₇]\n      -- Combine the results\n      rw [h₃, h₄, h₅]\n      <;> ring_nf\n    -- Combine the results to get the final answer\n    have h₃ : (log b - log a) + (1 / a - 1 / b : ℝ) = (log b + 1 / a - log a - 1 / b : ℝ) := by\n      ring_nf\n    linarith\n  -- Use the result to conclude the proof\n  rw [h₁]",
      "\n          exact ne_of_gt h₄)\n      · -- Prove that 1/x^2 is integrable on [a, b]\n        apply Continuous.intervalIntegrable\n        exact Continuous.div continuous_const (continuous_pow 2) (fun x hx => by\n          have h₂ : a ≤ x := by\n            cases' hx with hx₁ hx₂\n            linarith\n          have h₃ : x ≤ b := by\n            cases' hx with hx₁ hx₂\n            linarith\n          have h₄ : 0 < x := by linarith\n          have h₅ : (x : ℝ) ^ 2 ≠ 0 := by positivity\n          exact h₅)\n    rw [h₁]\n    have h₂ : ∫ x in a..b, (1 / x : ℝ) = Real.log b - Real.log a := by\n      have h₃ : ∫ x in a..b, (1 / x : ℝ) = Real.log b - Real.log a := by\n        rw [← Real.log_div (by positivity) (by positivity)]\n        <;> simp [intervalIntegral.integral_comp_mul_left (fun x => 1 / x)]\n        <;> field_simp [Real.log_mul, Real.log_div, Real.log_rpow, ha.ne', hb.ne']\n        <;> ring_nf\n        <;> norm_num\n        <;> linarith\n      rw [h₃]\n    have h₃ : ∫ x in a..b, (1 / x ^ 2 : ℝ) = (1 / a - 1 / b : ℝ) := by\n      have h₄ : ∫ x in a..b, (1 / x ^ 2 : ℝ) = ∫ x in a..b, (x : ℝ) ^ (-2 : ℝ) := by\n        congr\n        ext x\n        field_simp [Real.rpow_neg, Real.rpow_two]\n        <;> ring_nf\n        <;> norm_num\n        <;> field_simp\n        <;> ring_nf\n      rw [h₄]\n      have h₅ : ∫ x in a..b, (x : ℝ) ^ (-2 : ℝ) = (1 / a - 1 / b : ℝ) := by\n        -- Use the fundamental theorem of calculus to compute the integral\n        have h₆ : ∫ x in a..b, (x : ℝ) ^ (-2 : ℝ) = ((-1 : ℝ) * (b : ℝ) ^ (-1 : ℝ)) - ((-1 : ℝ) * (a : ℝ) ^ (-1 : ℝ)) := by\n          -- Compute the antiderivative and evaluate at the bounds\n          have h₇ : ∫ x in a..b, (x : ℝ) ^ (-2 : ℝ) = ∫ x in a..b, (x : ℝ) ^ (-2 : ℝ) := rfl\n          rw [h₇]\n          -- Use the fundamental theorem of calculus\n          have h₈ : ∫ x in a..b, (x : ℝ) ^ (-2 : ℝ) = ((-1 : ℝ) * (b : ℝ) ^ (-1 : ℝ)) - ((-1 : ℝ) * (a : ℝ) ^ (-1 : ℝ)) := by\n            -- Compute the antiderivative and evaluate at the bounds\n            have h₉ : ∫ x in a..b, (x : ℝ) ^ (-2 : ℝ) = ∫ x in a..b, (x : ℝ) ^ (-2 : ℝ) := rfl\n            rw [h₉]\n            -- Use the fundamental theorem of calculus\n            norm_num [integral_rpow, ha.ne', hb.ne', Real.rpow_neg_one]\n            <;>\n            (try norm_num) <;>\n            (try field_simp [ha.ne', hb.ne']) <;>\n            (try ring_nf) <;>\n            (try norm_num) <;>\n            (try linarith)\n            <;>\n            (try simp_all [Real.rpow_neg_one])\n            <;>\n            (try field_simp [ha.ne', hb.ne'])\n            <;>\n            (try ring_nf)\n            <;>\n            (try norm_num)\n            <;>\n            (try linarith)\n          rw [h₈]\n        rw [h₆]\n        -- Simplify the expression\n        have h₉ : ((-1 : ℝ) * (b : ℝ) ^ (-1 : ℝ)) - ((-1 : ℝ) * (a : ℝ) ^ (-1 : ℝ)) = (1 / a - 1 / b : ℝ) := by\n          have h₁₀ : (b : ℝ) ^ (-1 : ℝ) = 1 / b := by\n            simp [Real.rpow_neg_one]\n          have h₁₁ : (a : ℝ) ^ (-1 : ℝ) = 1 / a := by\n            simp [Real.rpow_neg_one]\n          rw [h₁₀, h₁₁]\n          <;> ring_nf\n          <;> field_simp [ha.ne', hb.ne']\n          <;> ring_nf\n          <;> norm_num\n          <;> linarith\n        rw [h₉]\n      rw [h₅]\n    rw [h₂, h₃]\n    <;> ring_nf\n    <;> field_simp [ha.ne', hb.ne']\n    <;> ring_nf\n    <;> norm_num\n    <;> linarith\n  rw [h₀]",
